President Obama has announced his intent to appoint two individuals to key Administration posts in the Arctic Research Commission. The first appointee is Dr. Charles J. Vörösmarty, a Professor of Civil Engineering at the City College of New York. He has been a member of the Arctic Research Commission since 2006. The second appointee is Dr. Warren M. Zapol, Director of the Anesthesia Center for Critical Care Research at Massachusetts General Hospital. He has been a member of the Arctic Research Commission since 2008 and has conducted extensive research in Antarctica.